  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study investigated the impact of Endocuff-assisted colonoscopy on the adenoma detection
      rate at colonoscopy. This study involved patients undergoing elective screening or
      surveillance colonoscopy.

      Patients were randomized to undergo Endocuff or regular, high-definition colonoscopy before
      undergoing a second colonoscopy by the alternate method. The primary outcome measure was the
      detection rate for adenomas between patients who underwent Endocuff first and patients who
      underwent regular colonoscopy first.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
